{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"7f7b0f95-0904-4763-b090-635c55c67b6d","content":"","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01Hd71PUenGHEJuRKnWNZ6hY","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Providing K8s crash dump config"},"type":"function"}],"interactionId":"75b78dd9-2af3-42a0-9349-75ece5007cc6","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to configure automatic crash dump collection for a NativeAOT .NET 11 app running in Kubernetes. They have `createdump` installed at `/opt/tools/createdump`. Let me provide them with the necessary configuration.\n\nFor .NET NativeAOT crash dump collection, the key environment variables are:\n- `DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump=1` - enables automatic crash dump generation\n- `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType=4` - full dump (MiniDumpWithFullMemory). Values: 1=Normal, 2=WithHeap, 3=Triage, 4=Full\n\n\n- `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName` - path/pattern for the dump file\n- `DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath=/opt/tools/createdump` - points to the createdump tool location\n- `DOTNET_CreateDumpDiagnostics=1` - optional, enables diagnostics for createdump itself\n\nNow I'll put together the pod spec configuration with these environment variables and ensure the volume mounts are set up correctly.","outputTokens":380,"requestId":"4182:1EA9D4:645645D:6D8DCDB:69F16384"},"id":"4cc93f3e-72f0-4c8e-a217-c61fe5756305","timestamp":"2026-04-29T01:49:01.191Z","parentId":"df869274-4b85-49c3-b6ff-24c8f46cd9a6"}
