{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"5aac7f0a-2fd1-47e2-8500-de31dd5b9165","content":"Here are the pod spec changes for automatic crash dump collection with NativeAOT on .NET 11:\n\n```yaml\nspec:\n  containers:\n    - name: your-app\n      env:\n        # Enable automatic mini dump on crash\n        - name: DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump\n          value: \"1\"\n        # Dump type: 1=Normal, 2=WithHeap, 3=Triage, 4=Full\n        - name: DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType\n          value: \"4\"\n        # Path to the createdump tool (required for NativeAOT)\n        - name: DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath\n          value: \"/opt/tools/createdump\"\n        # Output path with PID in filename to avoid collisions\n        - name: DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName\n          value: \"/tmp/dumps/coredump.%p.%t\"\n        # Optional: enable createdump diagnostics logging\n        - name: DOTNET_CreateDumpDiagnostics\n          value: \"1\"\n      volumeMounts:\n        - name: dump-volume\n          mountPath: /tmp/dumps\n  volumes:\n    - name: dump-volume\n      emptyDir:\n        sizeLimit: 2Gi\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n\n- **`DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath`** — required for NativeAOT since `createdump` isn't bundled in the runtime directory.\n- **`%p` / `%t`** in the dump name expand to PID and timestamp, preventing overwrites on repeated crashes.\n- **`MiniDumpType=4`** gives a full memory dump; use `2` (WithHeap) for smaller files if storage is tight.\n- The `emptyDir` volume is ephemeral — for persistence, swap it for a PVC or ship dumps to object storage via a sidecar.\n- Make sure `/opt/tools/createdump` has execute permissions and the `SYS_PTRACE` capability if your security context restricts it:\n\n```yaml\n      securityContext:\n        capabilities:\n          add: [\"SYS_PTRACE\"]\n```","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"75b78dd9-2af3-42a0-9349-75ece5007cc6","outputTokens":529,"requestId":"4182:1EA9D4:6457FDC:6D8FCA9:69F1638D"},"id":"dfd4ca5f-7654-4067-8b4b-84102925ffca","timestamp":"2026-04-29T01:49:13.816Z","parentId":"8ee84eca-9bb7-4b8e-b7c4-c22283689209"}
